# i18n

- All user-visible strings via translation keys (`labelKey`, `titleKey`, `| translate`).
- Add every new key to **both** `public/assets/en.json` and `public/assets/bh.json` (single file per language).
- In TS, return key strings for labels (e.g. `statusLabel()` → `'portal.user.features.shipments.table.status.${status}'`).
- Do not embed English prose in templates when a key exists or should exist.

## Key tree (mirrors `src/app/` layers)

```
shared.*                          — shell chrome + form/table/confirm frameworks
guest.*                           — public pages (landing, sign-in, login, register)
portal.shell.{admin|user}.*   — portal badge in sidebar brand
portal.admin.nav.*                — admin sidebar
portal.admin.pages.*              — admin route titleKey
portal.admin.features.<feature>.* — admin feature (form, table)
portal.user.nav.*             — user sidebar
portal.user.pages.*           — user route titleKey
portal.user.features.<domain>.<feature>.* — user feature (form, table)
```

### Shared (`shared.*`)

| Path | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `shared.sidebar.*` | Portal sidebar chrome |
| `shared.topbar.*` | Portal + shared topbar widgets (theme, language, account) |
| `shared.form.common.*` | Form footer (`previous`, `next`), stepper pill aria (`validationState.notStarted` / `inProgress` / `valid` / `invalid`), field errors (`errors.*`) |
| `shared.table.common.*` | Table loading, empty, pagination, row actions |
| `shared.confirm.common.*` | Confirmation dialog cancel/confirm button labels (defaults; do not duplicate per feature) |

### Guest (`guest.*`)

| Path | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `guest.landing.*` | Landing page |
| `guest.signIn.*` | Portal picker |
| `guest.login.*` | User + admin login pages |
| `guest.register.*` | Company registration page chrome |
| `guest.register.form.*` | Register company stepper form |
| `guest.topbar.*`, `guest.footer.*` | Guest shell |

### Portal admin feature example

```
portal.admin.features.vehicles.form.fields.marka
portal.admin.features.vehicles.table.columns.marka
portal.admin.features.vehicles.table.deleteConfirm.title
portal.admin.features.dashboard.metrics.users.title
portal.admin.features.dashboard.quickActions.title
portal.admin.features.dashboard.actions.allUsers.description
portal.admin.nav.allVehicles
portal.admin.nav.sections.dashboard
portal.admin.nav.overview
portal.admin.pages.vehicles
```

Reuse existing nav label keys (`portal.admin.nav.allUsers`, etc.) for quick-action card titles; add `…dashboard.actions.*.description` only for helper text.

### Portal user feature example

```
portal.user.features.shipments.form.steps.type
portal.user.features.shipments.table.columns.id
portal.user.features.fleet.vehicles.form.fields.plateNumber
portal.user.nav.allShipments
portal.user.pages.allShipments
```

## Rules for new keys

1. **Do not** add feature strings under legacy roots (`forms.*`, `tables.*`, top-level `nav.*`, `pages.*`, `landing.*`, `login.*`).
2. **Admin vs user** — always under `portal.admin` or `portal.user` (never cross-import keys).
3. **Form defs** (`*.form.ts`) — keys under `…features.<feature>.form.*`.
4. **Table defs** (`*.table.ts`) — keys under `…features.<feature>.table.*`; use `shared.table.common.*` for shared table chrome. Destructive row actions: add `…table.deleteConfirm.title` / `…message` in the feature namespace; button labels use `shared.confirm.common.*` (see `confirm.mdc`).
5. **Route `data.titleKey`** — `portal.<portal>.pages.<pageId>`.
6. **Nav `labelKey`** — `portal.<portal>.nav.<itemId>`.
7. **Enum/select options** — colocate under the same feature subtree (e.g. `…form.vrstaVozila.putnicko`).

## Files

- Translations: `public/assets/en.json`, `public/assets/bh.json`
- Language switching: `shared/core/i18n/language.service.ts`
